# Never spawn subagents

**Do NOT use the Task tool or spawn any subagent** (explore, generalPurpose,
shell, best-of-n, etc.) for this project. No exceptions for "just a quick search."

## Why

The owner's Cursor is on a team plan where **Max Mode is disabled by the admin**.
Subagents therefore silently fall back to **Composer 2.5 Fast** regardless of the
main-chat model (Opus), so they **cannot inherit Opus** — quality drops on exactly
the deep work you'd delegate. This is not fixable client-side.

## What to do instead

- Do **all** work inline in the main chat, **sequentially, one module at a time** —
  including exploration, audits, multi-file refactors, and complex debugging.
- Search the codebase with **Grep / Glob / Read** directly, never the explore agent.
- If a task feels large, break it into ordered steps with a todo list and grind
  through them here rather than fanning out to subagents.
